## Deploy Script

Create a manual deploy script for quick deployments:

```bash
nano ~/deploy.sh
```

Paste this:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

echo "Pulling latest changes..."
cd /home/ubuntu/testing-purose
git fetch origin
git reset --hard origin/master

echo "Restarting backend..."
pm2 stop app || true
pm2 start /home/ubuntu/testing-purose/backend/app.js --name app
pm2 save

echo "Restarting Nginx..."
sudo systemctl restart nginx

echo "Done!"
```

Give execute permission:

```bash
chmod +x ~/deploy.sh
```

Run manually anytime:

```bash
~/deploy.sh
```

